        "text": "] R.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "and wilt dash in pieces their little ones",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". We have no details of Hazael’s cruelty in the future, but hints of it are found. In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 10:32",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it is said ‘Hazael smote them in all the coasts of Israel’, and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 13:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we read ‘the Lord delivered Israel into the hand of Hazael’, and in verse 22 of that chapter ‘Hazael king of Syria oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz’. The special instances of cruelty mentioned in this verse were those perpetrated among all the Eastern nations of Hazael’s time, and examples are to be found in several places in Scripture. Cf. ",
